of temperate and tropical reef fishes they are also exploring ways to apply such basic ecological information to the conservation and harvest of marine species including marine reserves artificial reefs and environmental impact assessment tags biodiversity marine reserves natural resource management oceans & coasts reefs temperate fish tropical fish 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
